LICENSE

R-Node is made up of a number of different elements. Various licenses
are used to ensure the right balance is struct for their use and the
creator's desires.

  * R-Node Client

    The R-Node client code, as found in the subdirectory 'client', is
    licensed under the GPLv3 license.

  * R-Node Server

    The R-Node server code, as found in the subdirectory 'server', is
    licensed under the LGPLv2.1 license.

  * R-Node Shared Code

    Most of the R-Node shared code, as found in the subdirectory 
    'shared', is licensed under the LGPLv3 license, reproduced at 
    the bottom of this file.

    Current exclusions are:

      * R Parser

        The R code parser, in the file 'shared/js/R/r-parser-internal.js'
        is based off Douglas Crockford's JavaScript implementation of
        a top-down parser (find the original at 
        http://javascript.crockford.com/tdop/tdop.html)

        License status is unknown, and probably needs to be rewritten.



